	(5463, 'X-Men and Power Pack (2005) #1', '', 'Power Pack returns... and this time they\'ve brought some very special friends! Marvel\'s merry mutants team up with our super-powered siblings for four more fun-filled all-ages adventures! \r\n\r\nIn this issue: It\'s Halloween, and the Power kids are about to get the scare of their lives as candy is replaced with claws! Even with the X-Man called Wolverine on their side, will Power Pack be able to defeat a savage foe in time for trick-or-treating? "Costumes on," kids! \r\n\r\n\r\n32 PGS./ALL AGES ...$2.99', 'cover', 'X-Men and Power Pack (2005) #1', 'http://gateway.marvel.com/v1/public/comics/2565'),
	(5464, '1 of 4 - 4XLS', '', '', 'story', 'X-Men and Power Pack (2005) #1', 'http://gateway.marvel.com/v1/public/comics/2565'),
	(5465, 'X-Men and Power Pack (2005) #2', '', 'When the Power kids head off to another of their father\'s scientific conventions, they gear up for one of the most nerd-tastic weekends ever. But things go from geeky to freaky when Dr. Henry P. McCoy unveils an amazing new invention at the convention... a device that certain members of the scientific community would stop at nothing to get their hands on! Power Pack teams up with the bouncing, blue-haired Beast for a tale of mind over matter! \r\n32 PGS./ALL AGES ...$2.99 ', 'cover', 'X-Men and Power Pack (2005) #2', 'http://gateway.marvel.com/v1/public/comics/3093'),
	(5466, '2 of 4 - 4XLS', '', '', 'story', 'X-Men and Power Pack (2005) #2', 'http://gateway.marvel.com/v1/public/comics/3093'),
	(5467, 'X-Men and Power Pack (2005) #3', '', 'They say life\'s a circus -- and the super-powered siblings of Power Pack couldn\'t agree more. But when the real circus rolls into town, the Power kids find out that there\'s big trouble lurking under the big top! And if the kids thought clowns were scary, just wait until they meet the blue-skinned, pointy-eared X-Man known as Nightcrawler! \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n32 PGS./All Ages ‚Ä¶$2.99 ', 'cover', 'X-Men and Power Pack (2005) #3', 'http://gateway.marvel.com/v1/public/comics/3207'),
	(5468, '3 of 4 - 4XLS', '', '', 'story', 'X-Men and Power Pack (2005) #3', 'http://gateway.marvel.com/v1/public/comics/3207'),
	(5469, 'X-Men and Power Pack (2005) #4', '', 'Julie finds herself starting to fall for the cutest boy in her science class... but it looks her dream date is about to turn into a nightmare! Will the X-Men\'s Cyclops be able to help the remaining members of Power Pack rescue their sister and defeat the most sinister adversary they\'ve ever faced? \r\n32 PGS./All Ages ...$2.99 ', 'cover', 'X-Men and Power Pack (2005) #4', 'http://gateway.marvel.com/v1/public/comics/3416'),
	(5470, '4 of 4 - 4XLS', '', '', 'story', 'X-Men and Power Pack (2005) #4', 'http://gateway.marvel.com/v1/public/comics/3416'),
	(36224, 'Iron Man and Power Pack (2007) #1', '', 'What\'s 50-feet-tall, nearly indestructible, and on a rampage through New York City? Iron Man calls it "Ultimo"... but to the members of Power Pack, it\'s just another super-jerk trying to ruin their day off! And while our young heroes join forces with everyone\'s favorite armored Avenger to bring down this mega-sized metallic monstrosity, are they missing something far more sinister going on behind the scenes? Does the action ever end?!? Not for Marvel\'s youngest heroes! \r\nAll Ages ...$2.99', 'cover', 'Iron Man and Power Pack (2007) #1', 'http://gateway.marvel.com/v1/public/comics/17285'),
